<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — choose one path</h2>
  <p class="sub">Three real paths. All three end at the same exit ticket: a defensible first systems diagram of Earth.</p>
  <div class="callout sketch-first">
    <div class="callout-title">Sketch first — no words</div>
    <p>Before the convention, your picture. Five minutes, alone: draw how Earth's parts connect — your way, pictures only, no words. Then three minutes with a partner: where do your drawings agree? Keep the sketch in your journal, dated. Now — the choice board below teaches the shared way scientists draw this, and you'll feel why the conventions exist: you just hit every problem they solve.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> {{ learningIntention | safe }}
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">A</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Diagram-first</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">On blank paper: sketch all four subsystems as labeled circles. Draw at least one arrow connecting two of them — with a verb on the arrow ("evaporates," "weathers," "absorbs"). Label one loop in your diagram as positive (+) or negative (−) and justify the sign in one sentence below.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Visual · Solo</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">B</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Pair-walk</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Pick one specific interaction with a partner — ocean ↔ atmosphere is a strong starter. Talk it through verbally: what flows from A to B, what flows back, what would happen if you removed one direction. Then both of you draw it independently and compare.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Verbal · Pair</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">C</div>
      <div class="choice-title">AI-coached</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Open the <a href="/ai-partners/systems-diagrammer/">Systems Diagrammer</a> in a new tab. Tell it you're new to systems diagrams and you want to build your first Earth one. Work through its questions — name one subsystem, then another, then an interaction. You draw on paper as you go; the partner stays Socratic. End with a feedback-loop sign question.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Conversational · Solo</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

